               <note type="biblioComments">OY lists 6 mss., none of which can be considered historic. Carullah 2080 (c791H in Konya) is listed by OY as being copied from an original but we could find no specific note to this effect on the text. There are a number of works with similar titles, and there is much work to be done in distinguishing them from one another. However, there is a definite unique work listed here under RG 821, with at least four mss. (Carullah 2070, Husein Celebi 448, Milli 489 and Shehit Ali 1344) being versions of the same text. N.B. OY also lists Shehit Ali 1344 under RG 817.</note>
